üü¢ Language ‚û° Java
üü¢ Topic ‚û° Conditional Statements Questions (Java Version)

Write a Java program to check whether a given number is even or odd.

Write a Java program to check whether a given number is even or odd without using the % operator.

Write a Java program to check whether a given number is divisible by 5 or not.

Write a Java program to check whether a given number is positive or non-positive.

Write a Java program to check whether a given number is a three-digit number or not.

Write a Java program to print the greater between two numbers. Print one number if both are the same.

Write a Java program to print the greatest among three numbers. Print one number if two or all are the same.

Write a Java program to check whether a given year is a leap year or not.

Write a Java program that takes the cost price and selling price of a product from the user. Calculate and print the profit or loss percentage.

Write a Java program to input an alphabet from the user and check whether it is uppercase or lowercase.

Write a Java program to take marks of 5 subjects from the user (marks out of 100, passing is 33). Display whether the candidate passed or failed.

Write a Java program to check whether a given alphabet is a vowel or a consonant.

Write a Java program to check whether a number is divisible by both 3 and 2.

Write a Java program to check whether a number is divisible by 7 or divisible by 3.

Write a Java program to check whether a number is positive, negative, or zero.

Write a Java program to check whether a character is an uppercase alphabet, lowercase alphabet, digit, or special character.

Write a Java program that takes the lengths of the three sides of a triangle and checks whether the triangle is valid or not.

Write a Java program to take a month number as input and display the number of days in that month.

Write a Java program to check whether the roots of a given quadratic equation are real & distinct, real & equal, or imaginary.

Write a Java program to input two dates from the user and print which one is greater or print "Same" if both are equal.

Write a Java program to check whether a number is divisible by both 2 and 3 but not by 5.

Write a Java program to check if a character is a vowel using logical OR.

Write a Java program to check whether a number lies between 10 and 100 (inclusive) using logical AND.

Write a Java program to check whether a year is not a leap year using logical NOT.
